questions.explanation:
## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical data governance in Snowflake at scale, combining masking, row-level security, and secure views in a multi-tenant setup.

## Key Concepts
- Dynamic data masking on PII columns
- Row access policies for tenant isolation
- Secure views per-tenant access
- Role-based grants and auditability
- Rollback and testability

## Code Example
```sql
-- Create masking policies for email and ssn
CREATE MASKING POLICY pii_email_mask AS (email STRING) RETURNS STRING ->
  CASE WHEN CURRENT_ROLE() IN ('ADMIN','TENANT_A_VIEWER') THEN email ELSE 'REDACTED' END;

CREATE MASKING POLICY pii_ssn_mask AS (ssn STRING) RETURNS STRING ->
  CASE WHEN CURRENT_ROLE() IN ('ADMIN','TENANT_A_VIEWER') THEN ssn ELSE 'REDACTED' END;

-- Apply masking policies
ALTER TABLE CURATED.CUSTOMERS MODIFY COLUMN EMAIL SET MASKING POLICY pii_email_mask;
ALTER TABLE CURATED.CUSTOMERS MODIFY COLUMN SSN SET MASKING POLICY pii_ssn_mask;

-- Create row access policy for tenant isolation
CREATE ROW ACCESS POLICY tenant_isolation AS (tenant_id STRING) RETURNS BOOLEAN ->
  CASE WHEN CURRENT_ROLE() IN ('ADMIN') THEN TRUE
       WHEN CURRENT_ROLE() = 'TENANT_A_VIEWER' THEN tenant_id = 'TENANT_A'
       WHEN CURRENT_ROLE() = 'TENANT_B_VIEWER' THEN tenant_id = 'TENANT_B'
       ELSE FALSE END;

-- Apply row access policy
ALTER TABLE CURATED.SALES ADD ROW ACCESS POLICY tenant_isolation ON (TENANT_ID);

-- Create per-tenant secure views
CREATE SECURE VIEW CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_A AS
SELECT SALE_ID, CUSTOMER_ID, AMOUNT, SALE_DATE
FROM CURATED.SALES
WHERE TENANT_ID = 'TENANT_A';

CREATE SECURE VIEW CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_B AS
SELECT SALE_ID, CUSTOMER_ID, AMOUNT, SALE_DATE
FROM CURATED.SALES
WHERE TENANT_ID = 'TENANT_B';

-- Grant permissions
GRANT ROLE TENANT_A_VIEWER TO USER TENANT_A_USER;
GRANT ROLE TENANT_B_VIEWER TO USER TENANT_B_USER;
GRANT SELECT ON VIEW CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_A TO ROLE TENANT_A_VIEWER;
GRANT SELECT ON VIEW CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_B TO ROLE TENANT_B_VIEWER;

-- Test queries
USE ROLE TENANT_A_VIEWER;
SELECT * FROM CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_A; -- Should return only tenant A data
SELECT EMAIL FROM CURATED.CUSTOMERS; -- Should show actual emails for tenant A

-- Rollback commands
ALTER TABLE CURATED.SALES DROP ROW ACCESS POLICY tenant_isolation;
ALTER TABLE CURATED.CUSTOMERS MODIFY COLUMN EMAIL UNSET MASKING POLICY;
DROP MASKING POLICY IF EXISTS pii_email_mask;
DROP MASKING POLICY IF EXISTS pii_ssn_mask;
DROP VIEW IF EXISTS CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_A;
DROP VIEW IF EXISTS CURATED.V_SALES_TENANT_B;
```

## Implementation Notes
- Test masking and row access policies separately
- Use CURRENT_ROLE() for dynamic access control
- Secure views prevent view definition exposure
- Always test rollback procedures in development
- Monitor access through ACCESS_HISTORY view
